        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-1690",
        "content": "It won't be division enough, in that awful day, that some of us have been beggars here, and some of us have been rich,--we shall not be judged by that poor accident, but by our faithful following of Christ.' Margaret got up, and found some water and soaking her pocket handkerchief in it, she laid the cool wetness on Bessy's forehead, and began to chafe the stone cold feet.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-normal_e-normal",
